" <div class=\"graphic\">",
"  <div class=\"figure\" style=\"width: 516px\">",
"   <div class=\"ttl\">",
"    Transport properties of different nephron segments",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 496px; height: 191px; background-image: url(data:image/jpeg;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    Passive permeability of the loop of Henle and distal nephron segments to sodium chloride, urea, and water. The generally low passive permeability to solutes (except for the descending limb) means that transport can occur only via carriers or channels. The urea permeability of the innermost part of the medullary collecting tubule is increased in the presence of ADH.",
"    <div class=\"footnotes\">",
"     ++: highly permeable; +: moderately permeable; &plusmn;: less permeable; 0: relatively impermeable.",
"    </div>",
"    <div class=\"reference\">",
"     Data from: Jamison, RL, Kidney Int 1987; 21:S43, and Sands, JM, Am J Physiol 1987; 253:F823.",
"    </div>",
"   </div>",
